Description. Head orange, occiput ranging from mostly orange with black restricted to area around foramen (
Fig. 1
) to mostly black with orange around posterior margin of eye (
Fig. 12
), ocellar triangle may be brownish, prementum orange to dark brown with ventral third orange, maxillary palp yellow. Mostly covered with microtomentum, face shiny with thin line of microtomentum below lunule and antenna. Frons with variable extent of microtomentum, from mostly covered with shiny spots lateral to ocelli (as in
Fig. 29
) to mostly shiny with patches of microtomentum at anterior corners and reaching anteriorly to orbital and ocellar bristles (
Fig. 26
). Ocellar bristles at level of anterior margin of median ocellus. Subvibrissal bristle and anterior genal bristles about 0.5 X length of vibrissa.

Thorax black, mostly covered with microtomentum. Proepisternum shiny, anepisternum with microtomentum along dorsal third and posterior third and in a thin line along anterior margin below spiracle, katepisternum with a shiny spot behind fore coxa, meron shiny, metapleuron shiny with a stripe of microtomentum between posterior spiracle and hind coxa. Mesoscutum sculptured (
Fig. 12
). Halter white, brownish below knob.

Abdominal syntergite 1 + 2 heavily sclerotized with a semicircular weakly sclerotized patch anteriorly, black, covered with microtomentum. Tergites 3–4 with heavily sclerotized bars medially, otherwise weakly sclerotized, tergite 5 weakly sclerotized (
Fig. 21
). Sternites weakly sclerotized.

Male postabdomen: Sternite 5 narrow anteriorly, posterior corners strongly divergent, posterior margin with a deep notch and interrupted row of setae, anterior apodeme broad, about as long as external portion, without keel (
Fig. 52
). Surstylus paddle-shaped. Hypandrial arms with ventral tab-like structures (
Fig. 24
). Pregonite small, discrete. Postgonite with lobes widely separated, anterior lobe broad, rounded, posterior lobe pointed. Basiphallus with long epiphallus, broad, transparent preepiphallus. Distiphallus with strongly curved spinose dorsal tube, distal portion long, broad apically (
Fig. 51
).
